title: BP, GOM oil spill disaster claims pending and processed by BP, World, July 05 2010
name: BP, GOM oil spill disaster claims pending and processed by BP, World, July 05 2010
description:
The poly shapefile shows number of claims filed by both private industry and individuals against BP due to BP's Deep Water oil well disaster. BP so far has processed claims worth $127 million, just a fraction of the cost of the oil disaster that has cost upwards of $3 billion to BP so far. The claims data is aggregated at county level and BP offers explanation of what they consider as factors involved in each claim. Thus a single claim may pertain to number of factors affecting an individual and/or private industry. See the source URL for more information. 
Interesting to note that there are over 470 counties involved in the claims process, most of which are from the Gulf states and yet quite a few of these are also from Georgia.

author.source: BP's DeepWater Horizon Oil Well disaster repsonse website
